Because of the word "and", the instruction can be divided in two sub-instructions: 1) "jump opposite left" and 2) "jump around left thrice"
1) "jump opposite left". The word "opposite", results in 2 repetitions of command LEFT, therefore, "jump opposite left" results in 1 LEFT LEFT JUMP command.
2) "jump around left thrice". The word "around" results in 4 repetitions, therefore, "jump around left" corresponds to 4 LEFT JUMP commands. Because of the word "thrice", "jump around left thrice" results in 3 x 4 = 12 LEFT JUMP commands.
